# lornu.ai - Cursor Rules

## Scope
This is a **satellite repository** for the Lornu AI web application:
- **Type**: Frontend web application (React + Vite + Bun)
- **Deployment**: AWS EKS via Flux CD (managed in private-lornu-ai hub)
- **Staging Domain**: `future.lornu.ai`
- **Registry**: AWS ECR (`lornu-web` repository)

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: React 18 + TypeScript
- **Build Tool**: Vite 6
- **Package Manager**: Bun (or npm/pnpm compatible)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4
- **UI Components**: Radix UI + Material UI
- **Runtime**: Node.js 18+ or Bun

## Development
- Run `bun install` (or `npm install`) to install dependencies
- Run `bun run dev` (or `npm run dev`) to start dev server
- Run `bun run build` (or `npm run build`) to build for production
- Health check endpoint: `/healthz` (required for Kubernetes)

## Deployment
- Container builds MUST use `--platform linux/amd64` (EKS requirement)
- Images pushed to: `{AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/lornu-web`
- Deployment manifests managed in `private-lornu-ai` hub repository
- Flux CD reconciles automatically from hub repo

## Standards
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Follow existing component patterns (Radix UI + shadcn/ui style)
- Maintain 70%+ test coverage
- Use TypeScript strictly
- Follow conventional commits

